---
/**
 * Competitive Intelligence Page
 * How to benchmark against competitors using real tools.
 */

import AdminLayout from "@/layouts/AdminLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "Competitive Intel";
const pageDescription =
  "How to benchmark site performance against competitors using PageSpeed Insights, CrUX, and WebPageTest.";
---

<AdminLayout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={pageDescription}
  activeSection="competitive"
>
  <!-- Context note -->
  <div class="mb-8 p-4 bg-(--surface-secondary) border border-(--border-primary) rounded-sm">
    <p class="text-sm text-(--content-meta)">
      Competitor performance data can only be obtained from public tools — there is no API that gives private access
      to another site's real-user metrics. This page explains how to run and interpret real competitive benchmarks.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- PageSpeed Insights -->
  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-6">PageSpeed Insights</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-(--border-primary)">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-3">What it shows</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-(--content-body)">
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Real field data (CrUX)</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">For any URL with sufficient traffic, PSI shows 28-day p75 field data for LCP, INP, CLS, FCP, and TTFB — the same data source used here</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Lab data (Lighthouse)</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">A controlled Lighthouse run on a throttled 4G connection — comparable across any two sites regardless of traffic volume</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Opportunities and diagnostics</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">PSI shows exactly what is slowing a page down — useful for identifying competitor weaknesses and confirming your own improvements</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-(--border-primary)">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-3">How to use it</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-(--content-body)">
          <ol class="space-y-3 list-decimal list-inside text-(--content-meta)">
            <li>Go to <span class="font-mono text-xs bg-(--surface-tertiary) px-1 rounded">pagespeed.web.dev</span></li>
            <li>Enter a competitor's homepage or key product page URL</li>
            <li>Compare their LCP / INP / CLS field data against your own CrUX results on the Performance Overview page</li>
            <li>Repeat for 2–3 top competitors and record results in a spreadsheet</li>
            <li>Re-run monthly to track whether the gap is widening or narrowing</li>
          </ol>
          <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Note on small sites</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Competitors with low traffic won't have CrUX field data. In that case, compare Lighthouse lab scores only — these are always available</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CrUX API direct -->
  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-6">CrUX API (Direct Queries)</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-(--border-primary)">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-3">Query any public origin</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-(--content-body)">
          <p class="text-(--content-meta)">The same CrUX API used on the Performance Overview page can be queried for any origin with sufficient traffic. Use <code class="text-xs font-mono bg-(--surface-tertiary) px-1 rounded">curl</code> or Postman:</p>
          <pre class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded font-mono text-xs text-(--content-heading) overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre-wrap">curl -X POST \
  "https://chromeuxreport.googleapis.com/v1/records:queryRecord?key=YOUR_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '&#123;"origin":"https://competitor.com"&#125;'</pre>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Response includes</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">p75 values and full histogram densities for LCP, INP, CLS, FCP, TTFB — broken down by device type when available</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-(--border-primary)">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-3">CrUX Dashboard</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-(--content-body)">
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Looker Studio template</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Google provides a free CrUX Looker Studio dashboard that plots 28-day CWV trends for any origin — no API key required</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Side-by-side comparison</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Clone the template, enter your domain and a competitor's domain, and it renders both trend lines on the same chart</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Historical data</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">The CrUX BigQuery dataset goes back to 2017 — useful for long-term competitive trend analysis</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WebPageTest -->
  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-6">WebPageTest</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-(--border-primary)">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-3">Visual comparison</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-(--content-body)">
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Side-by-side filmstrip</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">WebPageTest's comparison view shows a frame-by-frame filmstrip of your site vs. a competitor loading simultaneously on the same connection</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Same test conditions</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Both sites run from the same geographic location, device, and connection profile — controlling for variables that skew Lighthouse comparisons</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-(--border-primary)">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-3">Waterfall analysis</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-(--content-body)">
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Request-level detail</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">The waterfall chart shows each network request with DNS, connect, and transfer timing — pinpoints exactly what is slow</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Block third parties</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Block individual domains to measure how much each third-party script costs in load time</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-(--border-primary)">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-3">Test locations</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-(--content-body)">
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Match your audience</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Run tests from cities that match your actual user geography — East Coast US, West Coast US, or international locations as relevant</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Mobile emulation</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Use the "Moto G4" or similar preset on a 3G/4G throttled connection to simulate mid-range mobile conditions</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What to track -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-6">What to Track</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-(--border-primary)">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-4">Recommended benchmark scorecard</h3>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-(--border-primary)">
                <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 font-medium text-(--content-heading)">Metric</th>
                <th class="text-left py-2 pr-4 font-medium text-(--content-heading)">Tool</th>
                <th class="text-left py-2 font-medium text-(--content-heading)">Source</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-(--border-primary) text-(--content-body)">
              <tr>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">LCP p75</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">PageSpeed Insights</td>
                <td class="py-2">Field (CrUX)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">INP p75</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">PageSpeed Insights</td>
                <td class="py-2">Field (CrUX)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">CLS p75</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">PageSpeed Insights</td>
                <td class="py-2">Field (CrUX)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">Performance Score</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">Lighthouse / PSI</td>
                <td class="py-2">Lab</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">Start Render</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">WebPageTest</td>
                <td class="py-2">Lab</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-(--surface-secondary) p-6 rounded-sm border border-(--border-primary)">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-(--content-heading) mb-3">Competitive benchmarking cadence</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-(--content-body)">
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">Monthly snapshot</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Run PSI on 3–5 competitor homepages on the same day each month; log results in a spreadsheet to detect trends</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">After major competitor releases</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">If a competitor redesigns or re-platforms, re-run immediately — redesigns often cause CWV regressions you can capitalize on</div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-(--surface-tertiary) rounded">
            <div class="font-medium text-(--content-heading) mb-0.5">After your own optimizations</div>
            <div class="text-(--content-meta)">Re-run your own PSI immediately after shipping performance improvements, then again 4–6 weeks later to see field data update</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</AdminLayout>
